news.title: RWAs meet Haryana CM, raise structural problems in societies
news.para: ​​The members also raised structural problems in various residential complexes and demanded structural audits be made mandatory for all housing societies.

news.title: Maharashtra: To change housing society name in records, collector's nod not must
news.para: ​Justices Shahrukh Kathawalla and Milind Jadhav quashed and set aside a February 16, 2021 letter of the City Survey Officer (CSO), Chembur, refusing to mutate the name of Basant Vihar CHSL in revenue records for want of an NOC from the collector.

news.title: Rajasthan government to extend cut-off date for regularising colonies
news.para: According to an official, the government is planning to extend the last date for applications seeking regularisation of houses constructed on agricultural land in urban areas to December 31, 2018.

news.title: Bengaluru urban district has 6,000 illegal layouts
news.para: The Administrative Reforms Committee-2, which is headed by former chief secretary TM Vijay Bhaskar, said that many measures are needed to control the growth of unauthorised layouts.

news.title: No GST on leasing residential building as hostel: Karnataka HC
news.para: The lessee leased out the six-floor property with 42 rooms as hostel for providing long-term accommodation to students and working professionals with the duration of stay ranging from 3 months to 12 months.

news.title: IIT Madras researchers to identify new housing tech, help bring down construction costs
news.para: ​The 'Accelerator Affordable Sustainable Housing Accelerators' is an initiative of the Ministry of Housing and Urban Affairs to provide incubation and acceleration support to potential future technologies that are not yet market-ready (pre-prototype applicants) or to the technologies that are market-ready (post-prototype applicants).

news.title: Kerala CM to hand over keys of 320 houses
news.para: In the first phase construction of 222 houses was completed and keys were handed over to the beneficiaries. Construction of 320 houses was completed in the second phase of RAY spending Rs 33.79 crore.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Cidco invites applications for latest housing scheme
news.para: Instead, it has appealed to people to participate in its recently launched housing scheme in which it has made available 5,730 tenements in Taloja node that has better connectivity via Mumbai-Pune Expressway, railways and Navi Mumbai Metro.

news.title: Telangana at number four in projects registered with RERA
news.para: Latest data obtained by TOI from across India shows Telangana had 4,002 real estate projects registered with T-RERA by February and 2,017 registered agents.

news.title: Will bear structural audit cost of Chintels Paradiso towers, says builder
news.para: On February 14, the town and country planning department had written to the director of IIT-Delhi for conducting an audit of the buildings at Paradiso, where a vertical collapse of five living rooms led to the deaths of two residents on February 10.

news.title: Chintels Paradiso residents hold protest march, demand CBI inquiry
news.para: The protesters have demanded "immediate arrest" of the promoters and directors of Chintels India Ltd and the government officials who issued occupation certificates (OC) for the apartments. They were supported by residents of adjoining housing societies.

news.title: MMRDA halts Mumbai's salt pans development blueprint, no scrapping order
news.para: “We have not gone ahead with the plan to appoint a consultant. The bids have not been processed and the tender will lapse in some days. However, so far, no formal orders to scrap the plan have been issued,” said an official.

news.title: For four years, 114 buildings 'unsafe', but Noida authority yet to take any action
news.para: In July 2018, nine persons died when two buildings — a new one and another being constructed — collapsed in Shahberi village of Dadri.

news.title: Gurugram: Registration of sale deeds of all projects of Chintels to be stopped
news.para: “In light of this incident at Chintel Paradiso, all sub-registrars have been directed to refrain from registering any document related to any property in projects developed by Chintels India Ltd, Chintels Exports Pvt Ltd, Ashok Solomon and Intels India Pvt Ltd,” the letter read.

news.title: Haryana government to amend building bylaws
news.para: Senior officials in the chief minister's office (CMO) said work towards this direction has already begun and there is a possibility of bringing some changes ahead of the assembly session.
